A validation client for use with the Yubico validation API (version 2).
By default, it uses the Yubico YubiCloud validation platform, but can
be configured for another validation server. To use YubiCloud you need a
client ID and an API key that can be fetched from https://upgrade.yubico.com/getapikey.

== Usage

Add this to your pom.xml:

[source,xml]
 <dependency>
   <groupId>com.yubico</groupId>
   <artifactId>u2fserver-core</artifactId>
   <version>0.1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
 </dependency>

[source,java]
----
U2fServer u2fServer = new U2fServerImpl(mySimpleDataStore);

u2fServer.getRegistrationRequest(username, "http://localhost:8080");
u2fServer.processRegistrationResponse(
            new RegistrationResponse(registrationData, clientData, sessionId),
            System.currentTimeMillis()

u2fServer.getSignRequest(username, "http://localhost:8080");

u2fServer.processSignResponse(new SignResponse(clientData, signData, challenge, sessionId, appId));
----